Class ResponseData

java.lang.Object
client.ResponseData
public class ResponseData extends Object
Class encapsulates the Response from the API in an easily and standardized manner.

Author:

  • Constructor Details

    • ResponseData

      public ResponseData(Map<String,Object> map, int statusCode)
      Primary Constructor for ResponseData object. Map is the API response parsed into a easily accessable object.
      Parameters:
      map - Parsed API Response.
      statusCode - Status code of the http response.

    • ResponseData

      public ResponseData(Exception e)
      Secondary constructor. If API request resulted in an exception, the Class can still be instanciated with the information of the Exception. Message of the exception will be saved in class field message. Type of exception (class) will be saved in class field exceptionType.
      Parameters:
      e - Exception that occured during API Request
